column2: # Model 1: Nighttime Lights in 2013, Distance to water bodies, distance to roads, and distance to railroads

glm(formula = cbind(number_positive, numer_examined - number_positive) ~ 
    ntl_2013 + dist_to_water + dist_to_roads + dist_to_railroads, 
    family = binomial(), data = BCG_vaccination_UGA)
Null deviance: 848.76  on 393  degrees of freedom
Residual deviance: 769.40  on 389  degrees of freedom
# Model 2: all the above, without distance to roads

glm(formula = cbind(number_positive, numer_examined - number_positive) ~ 
    dist_to_water + dist_to_railroads + ntl_2013, family = binomial(), 
    data = BCG_vaccination_UGA)
Null deviance: 848.76  on 393  degrees of freedom
Residual deviance: 769.58  on 390  degrees of freedom
# Model 3: only distance to water and distance to railroads

glm(formula = cbind(number_positive, numer_examined - number_positive) ~ 
    dist_to_water + dist_to_railroads, family = binomial(), data = BCG_vaccination_UGA)
Null deviance: 848.76  on 393  degrees of freedom
Residual deviance: 776.71  on 391  degrees of freedom

glm(formula = cbind(number_positive, numer_examined - number_positive) ~ 
    ntl_2013, family = binomial(), data = BCG_vaccination_UGA)
Null deviance: 848.76  on 393  degrees of freedom
Residual deviance: 840.58  on 392  degrees of freedom
# we will use Model 4 to predict (because we only know how to predict with raster data) and Model 2 for the  regression with spatially-correlated fixed effect
